<document>
	<title>The visibly fatty liver.</title>

	<author>Griscom-N-T.</author>
	<author>Capitanio-M-A.</author>
	<author>Wagoner-M-L.</author>
	<author>Culham-G.</author>
	<author>Morris-L.</author>

	<source>Radiology. 1975 Nov. 117(2). P 385-9.</source>

	<abstract>Fatty infiltration of the liver has been identified
   roentgenographically in several young children. Awareness of this
   possibility will sometimes allow a radiologist to contribute to the
   understanding of the patient&apos;s metabolic and nutritional state. If a
   child&apos;s liver is shown to be abnormally radiolucent, cystic fibrosis
   should be considered.</abstract>

